Trapped and Alone    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is my first LOTR deck i am posting.  I like dwarves but i can&#39;t figure out how to win at least most of my games with them.  So I have turned to Decktech to see if i can get some help.<br>
<br>
Fellowship<br>
First i usually bid 1 or 2 since i didn&#39;t put any burden removal in.  I usually go second but if i can go first i do.  Gloin is usually unstoppable before i go underground.  I double move only when i know im ok. If u play carefully you might be able to move in front of your oppenent.<br>
<br>
Shadow<br>
I usually play some cheap guys and start saving the orc commander and overseers for site 4 and 5 in the begining.  At site 4 5 they are usually are at your site so most of the time 2 companions have to exert.  You can usually make your opponent stop at site 4.  If u dont u can easily kill him.  The trapped and alone work soooo well.  If u have extra twilight them play coming for the ring to see ifrimbazelan cause some more wounds. The goblins are there to add a swarn feel and twilight.  If u have to fight at site 9 watch out for the direct archery after u exert to wound in the manuever phase when they haver less the 4 companions. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
